summary: Okay you know something I just loved and still love about the Marvel fandom? Especifically the MCU fandom?? Superfamily I just...
body:
Okay you know something I just loved and still love about the Marvel fandom? Especifically the MCU fandom??

Superfamily

I just loved it. I just love it. It’s awesome. Tony and Steve having their son Peter. It’s great and full of fluff (also angst but that’s something else).

And after the chaos of Civil War and Infinity War people didn’t killed that hashtag,no no no,they either ignored the canon or maked something new.

That something is: Tony and Steve divorced,both found new loves (for Steve the obvious choice is Bucky and for Tony it was either Pepper or Strange [mostly Strange]) and then Peter got four dads (or three dads and one mom [Pepper]).

It was just… So great and heartwarming for me… I just…. I just love it.

I love this. Let’s include Morgan please.

summary: Ok but imagine little Morgan Stark starting to grow up, starting to forget little bits of her father. Little details about him,...
body: Ok but imagine little Morgan Stark starting to grow up, starting to forget little bits of her father. Little details about him, but she always remembers how sweet he was to her, how amazing of a father he was, how he could always make her happy.Then she remembers the message he left that they watched at the funeral. She watches it again, now old enough to understand everything, and she just starts crying because she misses her father so much.

summary: I hate all anti Tony posts
body:
I hate all anti Tony posts

All these anti Tony people make him out to be a villain or stupid or just completely selfish and self absorbed. People are still going on about him making weapons for Stark Industries. Tony was following in his Father’s footsteps, of course when he saw the negative impact his weapons caused he stopped all production and began focusing on the technology side to help people in safer ways. And don’t forget that he wasn’t selling weapons on the black market, that was Obadiah Stane and of course it took him some time to figure out that he couldn’t be trusted. Tony knew Obie for a long time but when he did find out he didn’t hesitate to stop him.
